title: Claude Monet Water Lilies Foldable Tote
description:
Foldable Tote developed from Claude Monet’s Water Lilies, 1906, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

“One instant, one aspect of nature contains it all,” said Claude Monet, referring to his late masterpieces, the water landscapes that he produced at his home in Giverny. These works focused on a single, timeless motif—water lilies.

  • Dimensions: 16 in. x 26 in.  Folded:  4.5 x 5 in.
  • Materials: 100% Polyester.
  • Hand wash, hang dry.
  • Folded Tote has small clip to link to a key chain.
